Jesus Castro from Acevedo town, Huila region produced the most interesting Colombian coffee of my whole coffee career. It is bright, delicate and has notes of mint, star fruit and grapes. 
We cupped this coffee in Acevedo almost year ago during our Colombian trip and some of us even thought this coffee had a processing defect. 
Taste was unexpected and had us to return to this cup over and over again until it was empty, and we cupped it again, and again. 
Since there was only 100kg of parchment of this Colombia variety and ended up as  one bag of greens It became smallest microlot we bought this year. 
Not all beautiful things last forever and the last roast batch of it was delivered to @auricoffee in Punavuori. This morning they had three 250g bags left for sale and also some of it to be brewed on site. Go and ask for one.  I hope to be able to get more of this same coffee from upcoming crop.
